338
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:54,200
Because it's not like we're drowning in great candidate sites.

339
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:58,560
So the food thing, I think, like, that's an access issue and needs to be taken seriously.

340
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:02,100
But, yeah, if the bar's in slightly the wrong place.

341
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:05,600
It's also a thing you can work on, right?

342
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:12,020
Like, if we went back to site and we said, hey, you know how you sold approximately 3,000 baguettes or something?

343
00:20:12,020 --> 00:20:15,640
You know, because I think we do tend to eat on site quite a lot.

344
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:16,980
You know how you sold all these baguettes.

345
00:20:16,980 --> 00:20:19,540
If you did it again, would you mind putting a vegan wall on?

346
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:20,840
You'll sell another 200.

347
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:23,760
Then that's a good starting point for negotiation.

348
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:24,660
Yeah, true.

349
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:29,740
And you can't ask them to move the bar around because that would involve, like, JCBs and stuff.

350
00:20:29,740 --> 00:20:37,420
Yeah, I did wonder if where we erred in the bar is because it was a bit of a thoroughfare for getting between places and was sometimes very crowded.

351
00:20:37,420 --> 00:20:41,420
Maybe we needed to keep a bit of a channel there so people could actually get through.

352
00:20:41,420 --> 00:20:49,080
Because I'm sure I inadvertently stood in front of people and probably inadvertently stood in front of people in scooters who were trying to get around without going outside.

353
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:50,800
So that's another possible issue.

354
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:53,820
But yeah, generally, like, would we go back to Belfast?

355
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:55,480
Oh, God, yes, in a heartbeat.

356
00:20:55,480 --> 00:21:02,940
Yeah, if it was a viable place to go, I would quite happily go back to that venue on an Easter weekend.

357
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:06,120
It was, I think, generally very good for Eastcom.

358
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:14,660
And do you think it ended up being more expensive, significantly more expensive than a mainland UK one or not so much?

