00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:48,240
Sure, but I could easily have spent £100 on drinks in that bar over two nights and that is rather more than my usual alcohol budget at an Easter con.

390
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:52,240
And so, although I'm not saying it was bad value, it was definitely higher outlay of money.

391
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:58,760
Yes, so the convention was expensive for me, but I think every single individual thing I purchased was good value for money.

392
00:23:58,760 --> 00:23:59,980
Yeah, that's a good way of putting it.

393
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,660
I think that's the point.

394
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:07,400
So I just had, I just ate and drank far better than I normally do.

395
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:10,640
And also I saved all my lunches, so I didn't have to spend any money on lunches.

396
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:22,540
I think you had, it sounds like there was a much higher discretionary spend, but in terms of travel and hotels, which are the kind of non-negotiable bit, it's not actually too much different than many bits of the UK.

397
00:24:22,540 --> 00:24:27,120
If I wasn't staying in the main con hotel, and that's pretty unusual for me.

398
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:31,480
So it would have been £40 a night more in the convention hotel.

399
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:37,120
Although I think we probably have got about £40 less worth of breakfast, so that seems fine.

400
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:38,660
Not quite £40.

