00:32:46,540 --> 00:32:49,940
And I don't know if we talked about this on the live episode, but I wanted to talk about games.

550
00:32:49,940 --> 00:32:51,960
When do you not want to talk about games?

551
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:54,220
Games at the EasterCon or games generally?

552
00:32:54,220 --> 00:32:55,460
Games at the EasterCon.

553
00:32:55,460 --> 00:33:07,160
So I, this EasterCon is the first EasterCon I remember having role-playing games and social deduction games on the program as actual programmed items.

554
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:09,340
And I thought that was wonderful.

555
00:33:09,340 --> 00:33:11,360
I think it went, I think it worked really well.

556
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:13,700
I think, I thought the games room was pretty good.

557
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:16,940
It was run for them by a local game shop with volunteers.

558
00:33:16,940 --> 00:33:20,340
Yes, I think this is a very good wheeze.

559
00:33:20,340 --> 00:33:29,740
And I think that is a good wheeze, but I think kind of my family walked in and they immediately suggested a stupid party game for us to play,

560
00:33:29,740 --> 00:33:38,020
which probably wouldn't be a likely choice for any family at the EasterCon, but certainly wasn't really a very good choice for us.

561
00:33:38,020 --> 00:33:42,620
And then we found a kind of headbanging numbery game.

562
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:45,860
And so I did, I did play a stupid party game the other day that I liked.

563
00:33:45,860 --> 00:33:49,700
But, but no, so I thought it was a really good idea.

564
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:51,880
And I think that probably is a good model that works quite well.

565
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:59,860
If you can get a game shop that is attached to a games club who will all come in and volunteer in return for their badges and wouldn't otherwise be at the con.

566
00:33:59,860 --> 00:34:01,320
Like a good bet to me.

567
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:03,520
It ran on weekend.

568
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:04,180
It was pretty good.

569
00:34:04,180 --> 00:34:08,140
They had quite a lot of games, including, you know, I mean, I like games rooms generally.

570
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,220
So, you know, I thought this one was fine.

571
00:34:10,220 --> 00:34:21,520
I think having a games club run the games room was very good because I think it divorced the games room from the culture of games rooms at Eastercons.

572
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:32,800
And I think that was good because as someone who very much likes games, but finds the games room at Eastercon has been sometimes extremely insular and not very welcoming.

573
00:34:33,380 --> 00:34:40,260
I think having a company come in that didn't have that baggage, but did love games, who was like just happy to run games and be gamers.

574
00:34:40,260 --> 00:34:41,600
That was very nice.

575
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:43,860
Yeah, I thought the games room worked very well.

576
00:34:43,860 --> 00:34:49,340
And it was interesting to me in the light of like the Zucon run we did at Glasgow, where that's one of the scenarios.

577
00:34:49,340 --> 00:34:57,540
Like I actually thought having the dealer in the dealer's room who was selling games be the same people that were running the games room was nice.

578
00:34:57,540 --> 00:35:01,940
Because obviously that means that if you play games in the game room, they might be able to sell it to you in the dealer's room.

579
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:04,420
And yeah, there's there's some interesting.

580
00:35:04,420 --> 00:35:08,360
I thought being able to sell them to you straight there in the game room was a perfectly good idea.

581
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:09,660
It also works.

582
00:35:09,660 --> 00:35:10,240
Yeah.

583
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:10,560
Yeah.

584
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:10,720
Yeah.

585
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:19,160
Because Glasgow did this West End Games, which is based in Glasgow, ran a bunch of the gaming at the Glasgow Worldcon.

586
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:25,200
And I would quite like to see Eastercons pursue this more vigorously, because I think it might be an absolutely fantastic idea.

587
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:31,260
But I also think it might mean that you introduce the gaming communities in various cities to Eastercon.

588
00:35:31,260 --> 00:35:33,740
And then they might tell people about Eastercon.

589
00:35:33,740 --> 00:35:36,620
So I think it might also be advertising listeners.

590
00:35:36,620 --> 00:35:50,200
It has an issue, which is that we have a bunch of other areas of the convention where it would be possible to give people privileged access to sell to our members in return for them doing something for the con.

591
00:35:50,200 --> 00:35:57,100
And we tend to not do that because we've had bad experiences, obviously, in the past, but probably a very long time ago.

592
00:35:57,100 --> 00:35:58,740
So this might not matter.

593
00:35:58,880 --> 00:36:09,840
When also, I think part of the thing is that to run a good games room, you need a good games library and asking a member to bring a good games library and stay in the games room all weekend is very different to asking like a local games cafe to do it.

594
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:13,360
So I think that's another element.

595
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:18,080
But this is because this is also largely how games conventions do it.

596
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:30,140
Not entirely, but you'll often see at games conventions that you'll often see at games conventions that like shops run or not shops necessarily, but cafes run the board game library.

597
00:36:30,140 --> 00:36:31,100
Yeah.

598
00:36:31,340 --> 00:36:31,840
Yeah.

599
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:44,260
I mean, I think the thing we are that specifically happened at Belfast is that it wouldn't be feasible really for the people who normally do the provide a library of games to do it because it was in Belfast.

600
00:36:44,260 --> 00:36:46,300
And so that might have meant by necessity.

601
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:48,860
We have to go and talk to someone who doesn't need to bring them across the ocean.

602
00:36:48,860 --> 00:36:58,100
I noticed there are also snag tights were dealing at Belfast, which is a very nice idea, but I don't think they actually had much stock.

603
00:36:58,220 --> 00:37:08,040
They were sort of there in a sort of more promotional way and to talk to people and to come back next year because it wasn't really feasible for them to bring a whole load of tights in different sizes over to Belfast.

604
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:15,100
And that might also be the case, actually, that selling may not be the solution for them for East to come, but they did have a lovely time.

605
00:37:15,100 --> 00:37:16,020
So, yeah.

606
00:37:16,020 --> 00:37:16,740
So it's interesting.

607
00:37:16,740 --> 00:37:22,240
So I would be, I mean, I have a feeling that we've done this with a games shop before, but can't remember.

608
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:26,940
But I think what it sold was presumably the games company.

609
00:37:26,940 --> 00:37:37,940
Well, I hope they did well out of it because what I wonder is whether we've talked to the games shops and cafes before, but they haven't known if it would actually be a viable thing for them to do.

610
00:37:37,940 --> 00:37:41,080
Because they don't know like what the arrangements are between do we guarantee them sales?

611
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:45,520
Did they just come along knowing they'd sell some games on a quiet weekend for them, etc.

612
00:37:46,940 --> 00:37:48,060
Yeah, I went in the games room.

